---
description: Express API conventions
globs:
  - "server/**/*.js"
alwaysApply: false
---
- Structure: routes/ define endpoints only, controllers/ handle req/res,
  services/ hold business logic, db/ holds queries — don't mix these layers.
- All monetary values stored as integers (paise/cents), never floats.
- Every write endpoint that touches maintenance dues, expenses, or payments
  must be wrapped in a transaction.
- Auth middleware must run before role-check middleware, on every protected
  route — no route should skip both "just this once."
- Validate all input (use zod or similar) before it reaches a service layer.
- Log admin/treasurer actions that touch money or role changes (basic audit
  trail) — don't silently allow edits to financial records.